<subSubSection pageId="86" pageNumber="87" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1436,620,719]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
Two genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Calvert" authorityYear="1901" box="[323,418,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lestidae</taxonomicName>
occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[527,623,621,647]" name="Ecuador" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach in Brewster" authorityYear="1815" box="[634,704,622,647]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[634,704,622,647]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Lestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a large genus with 45 New World species, although only four species are recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[430,526,657,683]" name="Ecuador" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. They are large to medium-sized damselflies that perch with the wings out at an angle.
</paragraph>
